---
---

<section class="py-20 sm:py-28 bg-navy-light">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">The Problem</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white">What's slowing your firm down every month</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mt-4 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Most of the work that keeps your team late isn't accounting - it's the admin around it. Chasing clients, re-entering data, answering the same questions, and scrambling before deadlines.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-error/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-error" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Hours wasted chasing clients</h3>
        <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Your staff sends reminders, checks who replied, follows up again. Skilled accountants spend their time on admin instead of billable work.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-warning/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-warning" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12h6m-6 4h6m2 5H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Manual data entry from documents</h3>
        <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Invoices, receipts, bank statements - your team types data from PDFs and photos into spreadsheets and accounting software, one document at a time.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-blue/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8 12h.01M12 12h.01M16 12h.01M21 12c0 4.418-4.03 8-9 8a9.863 9.863 0 01-4.255-.949L3 20l1.395-3.72C3.512 15.042 3 13.574 3 12c0-4.418 4.03-8 9-8s9 3.582 9 8z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Same questions, over and over</h3>
        <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
          "Did you get my invoice?" "When is the filing deadline?" "What documents do I need?" Your team answers the same things every week.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-warning/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-warning" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 17v-2m3 2v-4m3 4v-6m2 10H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Reports get pushed to the end</h3>
        <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Building summaries and status reports is important but never urgent - until a deadline hits. Then it's a scramble to figure out where things stand.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card md:col-span-2 lg:col-span-2">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-error/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-error" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4 6h16M4 12h16M4 18h7" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Work scattered across WhatsApp, email, Excel, and memory</h3>
        <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
          There's no single place to see who sent what and what's still missing. Important things live in chat threads, email inboxes, spreadsheets, and someone's head. When that person is out - nobody knows the status.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
